#Conceptual Instagram – Intelligent Feed Algorithm

> An innovative Instagram prototype where user feed is powered by dynamic algorithmic ranking — optimized using relevance, engagement, and user-interest profiling.

---

## 🧠 Core Idea

Instead of showing posts in a strict chronological order, this project implements a **custom recommendation algorithm** that personalizes feed content using multiple parameters like:

- User engagement history
- Hashtag relevancy
- Content freshness
- Creator-user interaction score
- AI-based content tagging (Optional)

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🖼️ Post & story uploading (image/video)
- 👥 Follow/Unfollow users
- ❤️ Like, comment, and save posts
- 📊 Feed sorting by smart algorithm
- 🔍 Discover & explore via tags
- 🔒 JWT-based authentication
- 📈 Admin dashboard (optional)

---

## 📊 Algorithm Flow (Simplified)

```mermaid
graph TD
A[User opens feed] --> B[Fetch recent posts from followed users]
B --> C[Calculate engagement score]
C --> D[Analyze hashtag relevance & AI tags]
D --> E[Rank posts based on interest]
E --> F[Display top-N results in feed]
````

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Category            | Tools Used                  |
| ------------------- | --------------------------- |
| 🧑‍💻 Frontend      | React.js, TailwindCSS       |
| 🛠 Backend          | Node.js, Express.js         |
| 🗃 Database         | MongoDB                     |
| 🔐 Auth             | JWT, Bcrypt                 |
| ⚙️ ML/AI (Optional) | TensorFlow\.js / OpenAI API |
| 📦 Deployment       | Vercel / Render / Railway   |

---

## 🧪 Algorithm Logic (Scoring Example)

```js
score = (likes * 0.4) + (comments * 0.3) + (saves * 0.2) + (tagRelevance * 0.1);
```

You can expand this logic using collaborative filtering or content-based filtering.

